725042f-b.title: Queens: 14th Street - 26th Avenue
725042f-b.text:
14th Street, south of, adjoining, and at the S.E. corner of
26th Avenue, showing three old mansions. The second house from
the right, adjoining the corner, is the Trowbridge house of 1873.
26th Avenue was formerly known after the family that owned the
house. View 2 shows the Trowbridge house and the one south of
it; view 3 also shows the Trowbridge house by itself; and view 44
the house at the S.E. corner of 26th Avenue, seen on the left in
view 1.
Views 1,2: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  192S
MAY BE REPRODUCED
Views 3,4:  P. L. Sperr
NO REPRCDUCTIONS  March 13, 1931
